In this file, I exported some of the bug reports I made in my previous projects: Tezbor and Tezride. 
These reports from authentication of 'Tebor Driver' mobile app were actually uploaded to the Azure DevOps. As long as I don't have access to task manager, I just mockup the bug report.



Evironments: Android & iOS

Description:
Phone number field allows submission with less than 9 digits without any validation feedback.

Given:
the user is on the phone number entry screen
When:
the user enters fewer than 9 digits and presses "Next"
Then:
the application does not respond
Actual Result:
No warning or error message is shown
App appears frozen or unresponsive
Expected Result:
A validation error message should be displayed indicating the phone number is incomplete
User should not proceed until a valid phone number is entered










Description:
Phone number input allows non-numeric characters.

Given:
the user is on the phone number entry screen
When:
the user enters letters or special characters
Then:
the input is accepted without error
Actual Result:
Letters and special characters can be entered
No validation error is shown
Expected Result:
Phone number field should accept digits only
Invalid characters should be blocked or trigger validation error








Description:
Name and surname fields allow submission with only whitespace.

Given:
the user is on the "About the Driver" page
When:
the user enters only spaces in name or surname fields
Then:
the fields are accepted as valid input
Actual Result:
User can proceed with invalid name/surname
Expected Result:
Fields should reject whitespace-only input
Validation message should request a valid name/surname









Description:
Email field does not perform basic format validation.

Given:
the user is on the "About the Driver" page
When:
the user enters "   @" or "@ " in the email field
Then the input is accepted
Actual Result:
Invalid email formats pass validation
Field only validate if there is @
Expected Result:
Email field should validate correct email format
Invalid formats should display an error message










Description:
Invited-by phone number field allows non-numeric input.

Given:
the user is on the "About the Driver" page
When:
the user enters letters or special characters in the invited-by field
Then:
the input is accepted without validation
Actual Result:
Invalid characters are allowed
No error message is shown
Expected Result:
Field should accept digits only
Invalid input should be blocked or validated









Description:
Invited-by phone number field is optional but not labeled as such.

Given:
the user is on the "About the Driver" page
When:
the user views the invited-by phone number field
Then:
there is no indication that the field is optional
Actual Result:
Field is optional but unclear to users
Partial input triggers errors without context
Expected Result:
Field should be labeled as "Optional"
Validation should trigger only if the user starts entering data







Description:
Privacy and Policy section opens with no visible content.

Given:
the user is on the "About the Driver" page
When:
the user opens the Privacy and Policy section
Then:
the content area is empty
Actual Result:
No text or information is displayed
Expected Result:
Privacy and Policy content should be displayed properly







Description:
Next button remains enabled regardless of form completion.

Given:
the user is on the "About the Driver" page

When:
required fields are incomplete

Then:
the Next button remains enabled

Actual Result:
User can tap Next without completing mandatory fields

Expected Result:
Next button should be disabled (blurred out) until all required fields are valid






Description:
Identification screen button design causes user confusion and incorrect flow.

Given:
the user is on the Identification page 

When:
the user sees "Open Camera" (white) and "Next" (green) buttons

Then:
the user taps "Next" expecting to proceed

Actual Result:
"Next" button appears primary but is not used for photo submission
User proceeds by pressing "OK" after photo capture, not "Next"

Expected Result:
Primary action should be "Open Camera"
"Next" button should be disabled or removed until photo is captured
Flow should be consistent and clear











Description:
Help ("?") icon shows active state but does not respond to taps.

Given:
the user is on the Identification page

When:
the user taps the "?" icon

Then:
nothing happens

Actual Result:
Icon appears interactive but is non-functional

Expected Result:
Icon should either be tappable and show help content
Or be visually disabled if not functional








Description:
App fails to inform user when camera permission is denied.

Given:
the user denies camera permission

When:
the app attempts to open the camera

Then:
no error or guidance is shown

Actual Result:
Camera does not open
User receives no explanation or instructions

Expected Result:
App should show a clear message explaining camera permission is required
User should be guided to enable permission in settings

And

Given the user goes to system settings without killing the app
When the user enables camera permission and returns to the app
Then the app starts the registration flow from the beginning







Description:
Previously received OTP remains valid after restarting or re-entering the phone number.

Given:
the user receives an OTP

When:
the user navigates back to phone number entry or closes the app

And:
enters the same phone number again

Then:
no new OTP is sent

Actual Result:
Old OTP can still be used to complete registration

Expected Result:
A new OTP should be generated for each new attempt
Old OTPs should be invalidated









Description:
OTP submission does not handle network loss correctly.

Given:
the user is on the OTP verification screen

When:
the network connection is lost

And:
the user submits the OTP

Then:
no network error message is displayed

Actual Result:
No error is shown
After reconnecting, registration does not continue automatically
User must re-enter the OTP manually

Expected Result:
Network error message should be displayed
App should retry or guide the user clearly after reconnection











